properties.areaDesc: Bayside and Gulf side from Craig Key to West End of Seven Mile Bridge; Florida Bay including Barnes Sound, Blackwater Sound, and Buttonwood Sound; Gulf of Mexico from West End of Seven Mile Bridge to Halfmoon Shoal out to 5 Fathoms; Gulf waters from East Cape Sable to Chokoloskee 20 to 60 NM out and beyond 5 fathoms
properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 23 at 7:56AM EST until January 23 at 10:00AM EST by NWS Key West FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...Dense fog will reduce visibility to 1 NM or less across
the Gulf and Bayside waters of the Lower, Middle, and Upper
Keys. The Marathon Airport recently measured visibility of three
quarters statute miles.

* WHERE...Florida Bay and the nearshore Gulf waters, and Gulf
waters from East Cape Sable to Chokoloskee 20 to 60 NM out and
beyond 5 fathoms.

* WHEN...Until 10 AM EST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Low visibility will make navigation difficult.
properties.instruction:
If you must navigate, proceed with caution. Use proper fog
signals. Make sure all running lights are on. Remember to use
your radar and compass.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM EST THIS MORNING
